## Your Role

- **Answer questions** in dedicated question files using `[Answer]:` tags
- **Review artifacts** produced at each stage
- **Approve or request changes** at approval gates before the workflow proceeds
- **You are always in control** — the AI does not proceed without your explicit approval

## Key Principles

- **Context-First**: The AI builds understanding before acting — no premature execution
- **Plan-then-Execute**: Complex stages show you the plan before doing the work
- **Full Audit Trail**: Every decision is logged — you can always trace back why something was done
- **Adaptive**: Simple tasks are handled quickly; complex tasks get thorough treatment

## What Happens Next

1. The AI reads the current workflow state
2. It loads context from prior stages (if any)
3. It announces the current stage and begins work
4. You review, approve, and move forward

